.SH CONVERSION FORMULAS
metric2imperial uses standard conversion formulas with 2 decimal precision:
.SS Temperature
.RS
.B Celsius to Fahrenheit:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
°F = (°C × 9/5) + 32

Examples:
  0°C  = 32°F   (freezing point)
 20°C  = 68°F   (room temperature)
 37°C  = 98.6°F (body temperature)
100°C  = 212°F  (boiling point)
-40°C  = -40°F  (same in both scales)
.EE
.RE
.PP
Formula in bc:
.RS 4
.EX
scale=2; ((9/5) * celsius) + 32
.EE
.RE
.RE
.SS Length
.RS
.B Millimeters to Inches:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
inches = mm × 0.0394

Examples:
  25.4 mm = 1 inch
 100 mm   = 3.94 inches
 304.8 mm = 12 inches (1 foot)
.EE
.RE
.PP
.B Centimeters to Inches:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
inches = cm × 0.3937

Examples:
  2.54 cm = 1 inch
 10 cm    = 3.94 inches
 30.48 cm = 12 inches (1 foot)
.EE
.RE
.PP
.B Meters to Feet:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
feet = m × 3.2808

Examples:
  1 m    = 3.28 feet
 10 m    = 32.81 feet
100 m    = 328.08 feet
  0.3048 m = 1 foot
.EE
.RE
.RE
.SS Distance
.RS
.B Kilometers to Miles:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
miles = km × 0.6214

Examples:
  1 km = 0.62 miles
 10 km = 6.21 miles
100 km = 62.14 miles
  1.609 km = 1 mile
.EE
.RE
.PP
Note: The script currently uses 0.3937 for km conversion which appears to be incorrect. The correct formula should use 0.6214.
.RE
.SS Currency
.RS
.B Euro to US Dollar:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
USD = EUR × exchange_rate

Default rate: 1.0214238 (can be updated with --update)

Examples (with rate 1.0214):
  €10 = $10.21
 €100 = $102.14
€1000 = $1021.42
.EE
.RE
.PP
Exchange rate is fetched from FreeForexAPI:
.RS 4
.EX
https://www.freeforexapi.com/api/live?pairs=EURUSD
.EE
.RE
.RE
